title: The French Connection, Austrian Economics and the Meaning Crisis with Two Engineers
description:
The Intersection of the Meaning Crisis and Austrian Economics

Karl (U. Berkeley in Engineering Physics) and Ira (U. Of Florida in Mechanical Engineeringand Masters at Duke in Fluid Mechanics) discuss the meaning crisis and what Austrian Economics might offer in terms of answers.

Engineering looks at how things work. 
Ira initially became interested in Austrian Economics through reading Ludwig Von Mises’ Human Action. Karl first read Friedrich Hayek and then found his way to Von Mises.
The free market system to some extent depends upon a moral people, a sense of the dignity and value of other individuals.
Since the resurrection of Jesus Christ, this idea of the value and dignity of each and every. Individual has percolated through history - had a great impact on the enlightenment.
The practice of agape bears much fruit.
The Foundation for Economic Education (https://fee.org)

Books and authors mentioned:
Ludwig Von Mises - Human Action
Friedrich Hayek - The Road to Serfdom
Gad Saad
Nassim Taleb
Sam Harris
Stephen Pinker
Jordan Peterson
Murray Rothbard
